//accumulator OR returnValue: gets assigned the return value of the callback function from the previous iteration.

// reduce(accumulator, currentElement, indexCurrentElement, arrayOnwhichReduceIsCalled)

function getRating(watchList){
  // Only change code below this line
  var averageRating;
  
  //Apllying filter for extracting movies whos director is "Christopher Nolan". Then fetching only imdbRating from each movie using map.

  let filteredList = watchList
  .filter(movie => (
    movie.Director === "Christopher Nolan"
  ))
  .map(movie => (
      {
        "imdbRating": parseFloat(movie.imdbRating)
      }
    ));

  const totalMovies = filteredList.length;

// Using reduce to calculate the sum of all imdbRatings.
  const sumOfimdbRating = filteredList.reduce((sum, imdbRatingObj) => sum + imdbRatingObj.imdbRating,0);

return sumOfimdbRating/totalMovies;
  // Only change code above this line
  return averageRating;
}
console.log(getRating(watchList));
